headline: Why Analysts See Centene’s Story Shifting Amid Margin Recovery Hopes and Medicaid Risks
summary: Centene's fair value estimate has been nudged higher from $39.41 to $39.94 per share, while the discount rate in valuation models has ticked down from 7.37% to 7.30%. This signals a slightly more constructive view on risk even as Street opinion grows more divided between bullish and cautious camps. These fine tuned inputs reflect a tug of war between optimism around Q3 execution and margin recovery and lingering concerns about Medicaid exposure, contract volatility, and the broader...
